The paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category, as it covers NLP and related topics. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category, as sentiment analysis is often used in search engines and recommendation systems. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category, as the paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for sentiment analysis. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible sub-category, as the paper deals with social media data. Finally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category, as sentiment analysis is a common application of AI techniques.
